<category><pattern>WNDEF ASSET</pattern>
<template>It is any property cash and cash equivalent or any other such items held by the business which result in an income</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>WNDEF liability</pattern>
<template>It is any debts owed or anything that results in the business spending money to maintain the same.</template>
</category>
<category><pattern>WNDEF Difference between a current asset and a non current asset</pattern>
<template>A current asset is going to be in the business for less than one financial year whereas a non current asset is going to be in the business for more than one financial year</template>
</category>
 
 <category><pattern>WNDEF current liability and non current liabilities</pattern>
<template>Current liabilities are going to be paid off within one financial year whereas non current liabilities are going to extend over one financial year</template>
</category>


<category><pattern>WNDEF expenses and purchases</pattern>
<template>Purchases are goods or services which the business buys so that they are resold whereas expenses are costs which the business pays for for smooth running of the business.</template>
</category>

<category><pattern>WNDEF three essential financial statements</pattern>
<template> The three essential financial statements include the statement of financial position,income statement and the cash flow statement</template>
</category>
 
<category><pattern>WNDEF Income statement</pattern>
<template>The income statement also known as the profit loss account shows the profit or loss made or suffered by the business</template>
</category>

<category><pattern>WNDEF statement of financial position </pattern>
<template>The statement of financial position basically shows a list of asset,liabilities and capital information of the business</template>
</category>

<category><pattern>WNDEF statement of cash flow </pattern>
<template> The cash flow statement shows how cash is used and earned in the business from operating investing and financing activities</template>
</category>
 

<category><pattern>WNDEF significance of the other income section </pattern>
<template> The other income section is responsible for picking up the information on the other incomes earned apart from that accruing from the main business of the company</template>
</category>
